        "![Top Skills Across Software, Specialized, and Common Skill Categories](images/top_skills.png){width=80% fig-align=\"center\" #fig-top-skills fig-alt=\"Bar chart showing the top skills across software, specialized, and common skill categories, with SQL being the most mentioned skill by a wide margin.\"}\n",
        "\n",
        "@fig-top-skills The top skills results shows that SQL, Data Analysis, Communication, and Python are among the most requested skills. That is a strong sign that employers want a mix of technical ability and business communication, not just coding alone. Tools like Excel, Power BI, Tableau, and dashboards also rank high, which reinforces that reporting, analysis, and decision support are major parts of these jobs. The presence of communication, project management, and business analysis skills suggests that employers value candidates who can manage projects and understand business needs, not just execute technical tasks. Overall, the skill demand analysis indicates a market that values a combination of technical proficiency, analytical thinking, communication, and business acumen.\n",
