        "\n",
        "@fig-top-skills-by-role The heatmap shows that skill demand clearly varies by role. For example, Data Analyst roles are strongly tied to SQL, Python, dashboards, and data analysis, while Oracle, SAP, and ERP roles lean more toward platform-specific and business process skills. At the same time, communication appears across multiple roles, not just analyst positions, which suggests it’s a core expectation regardless of specialization. Overall, while some technical skills are role-specific, there is a consistent need for both technical execution and the ability to communicate insights, depending on whether the role is more technical, operational, or business systems focused.\n",
